      "comment": "TIGER JEWEL (1) got it wrong when resuming but was very good last week when she raced three wide at this circuit and distance before boxing on for a 4.6m third. Fitter again and should get every chance from the ace draw in a race weakened by scratchings. SMALL INCOME (4) came from the back row when beaten less than 4m here last start. Good effort for second three back at Penrith. Can measure up off that effort. FOGWATCH (7) draws wider but is worth including following a respectable third at his most recent appearance. BOOMER SHANNON (9) is a long-time maiden but was only beaten 3.3m last start and draws for a trail so include.",
